<div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-8">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Privacy Policy</h1>
  
  <div class="prose prose-slate max-w-none">
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">Last updated: <%= Date.today.strftime("%B %d, %Y") %></p>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">1. Information We Collect</h2>
      
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">1.1 OAuth Authentication Data</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">
        When you sign in using Google, Twitter, or Facebook, we collect:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
        <li>Your email address (verified by the provider)</li>
        <li>Your name and profile picture</li>
        <li>OAuth provider ID and access tokens (encrypted)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">1.2 Usage Information</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">
        We automatically collect certain information when you use our Service:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
        <li>Browser type and version</li>
        <li>IP address</li>
        <li>Pages viewed and time spent on pages</li>
        <li>Session data</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">1.3 User-Generated Content</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Any reviews, comments, or other content you post on the Service.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">We use the information we collect to:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
        <li>Provide, maintain, and improve our Service</li>
        <li>Authenticate your account and manage your sessions</li>
        <li>Display your profile information and content</li>
        <li>Communicate with you about the Service</li>
        <li>Monitor and analyze usage patterns</li>
        <li>Detect, prevent, and address technical issues</li>
        <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">3. Data Security</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your data:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
        <li>OAuth access tokens are encrypted using ActiveRecord encryption</li>
        <li>Session tokens are signed and secured</li>
        <li>HTTPS encryption for all data transmission</li>
        <li>Regular security audits and logging</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mb-4">
        However, no method of transmission over the Internet is 100% secure. We cannot guarantee absolute security.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">4. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        We do not sell your personal information. We may share your information only in the following circumstances:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
        <li><strong>With your consent:</strong> When you explicitly agree to share your information</li>
        <li><strong>Legal requirements:</strong> When required by law or to respond to legal process</li>
        <li><strong>Protection of rights:</strong> To protect the rights, property, or safety of GamesReview.com, our users, or others</li>
        <li><strong>Business transfers:</strong> In connection with any merger, sale of assets, or acquisition</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">5. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        We use third-party OAuth providers (Google, Twitter, Facebook) for authentication. These services have their own privacy policies:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
        <li><a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Google Privacy Policy</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://twitter.com/en/privacy" target="_blank" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Twitter Privacy Policy</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.facebook.com/privacy/policy/" target="_blank" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Facebook Privacy Policy</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">6. Your Rights and Choices</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">You have the right to:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
        <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request a copy of your personal data</li>
        <li><strong>Correction:</strong> Request correction of inaccurate data</li>
        <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> Request deletion of your account and data</li>
        <li><strong>Data portability:</strong> Request a copy of your data in a portable format</li>
        <li><strong>Withdraw consent:</strong> Disconnect OAuth providers from your account settings</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">7. Data Retention</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        We retain your information for as long as your account is active or as needed to provide you services. 
        You may delete your account at any time, which will remove your personal data from our systems within 30 days.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">8. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Our Service is not intended for children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal information 
        from children under 13. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal information, 
        please contact us.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">9. International Data Transfers</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your own. 
        We will take appropriate measures to ensure your data is treated securely and in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">10. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any material changes by posting the new 
        Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last updated" date.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">11. Contact Us</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at: privacy@gamesreview.com
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-8 pt-4 border-t border-gray-200">
    <%= link_to "â† Back to Sign In", sign_in_path, class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800" %>
  </div>
</div>
